You can use the `Template Reference variable` for it like 

      &lt;mat-select disableRipple #second&gt;
        &lt;mat-option value=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/mat-option&gt;
        &lt;mat-option value=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Yes&lt;/mat-option&gt;
        &lt;mat-option value=&quot;2&quot;&gt;No&lt;/mat-option&gt;
      &lt;/mat-select&gt;
      &lt;mat-select *ngIf=&quot;second.value != 1&quot;&gt;
         &lt;mat-option value=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/mat-option&gt;
       &lt;/mat-select&gt;
[STACKBLITZ][1]


  [1]: https://stackblitz.com/edit/stackoverflow-if-value-is-selected-3rd-dropdown-is-show-7zm4bg

You must use `value` and not `ngModel` like this:

**HTML:**

    &lt;mat-form-field&gt;
      &lt;mat-label&gt;Is this partner a PEP?&lt;/mat-label&gt;
      &lt;mat-select disableRipple&gt;
        &lt;mat-option value=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Yes&lt;/mat-option&gt;
        &lt;mat-option value=&quot;2&quot;&gt;No&lt;/mat-option&gt;
      &lt;/mat-select&gt;
    &lt;/mat-form-field&gt;
    &lt;mat-form-field&gt;
      &lt;mat-label&gt;Does this partner blacklisted&lt;/mat-label&gt;
      &lt;mat-select disableRipple [(value)]=&quot;selected&quot;&gt;
        &lt;mat-option value=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Yes&lt;/mat-option&gt;
        &lt;mat-option value=&quot;2&quot;&gt;No&lt;/mat-option&gt;
      &lt;/mat-select&gt;
    &lt;/mat-form-field&gt;
    &lt;mat-form-field *ngIf=&quot;selected == 1&quot;&gt;
      &lt;mat-label&gt;Blacklist Name(s)&lt;/mat-label&gt;
      &lt;mat-select&gt;
       &lt;/mat-select&gt;
    &lt;/mat-form-field&gt;

**TS:**

    export class SelectValueBindingExample {
      selected = &#39;1&#39;;
    }

